<s> I actually expanded that from the more compact form and the reason for that is twofold.  </s>
<s> Firstly, empty elements in XML use a different form than elements with content and having this explict makes it clear which one are talking about.  </s>
<s> From an implementation point of view, the empty/non-empty cases are an important distinction.  </s>
<s> Secondly, we can use the answers from the empty-elements decisions that Jan wrote for property elements, to directly write down the answers to what statements are generated from the grammar: but maybe in the next version  </s>
